  "notes": "Central Bikol (Bikol Sentral) — Philippine language of the Bicol Region, written in the Latin script (the Abakada-derived alphabet a b k d e g h i l m n ng o p r s t u w y, extended for loans). Native three-vowel system /a i u/; /u/ surfaces as [o] in final syllables, which the orthography writes ⟨o⟩. /e/ is a marginal phoneme from Spanish loans. ⟨ng⟩ is the velar nasal /ŋ/. The palatal digraphs sy/ty/dy/ny/ly and the letters f, v occur only in Spanish and English loanwords. Glottal stop is phonemic but usually left unwritten (optionally ⟨'⟩ or a hyphen). Stress is contrastive and not consistently marked.",
